MAX: The year's been
over for a couple months.

12:18.321 --> 12:20.358
Well, not the fiscal year
of Penny.

12:20.657 --> 12:21.943
Suck it, taxpayers.

12:22.242 --> 12:23.949
You wiped Barnaby's mind

12:24.244 --> 12:25.484
just like you're trying to do
to me.

12:25.787 --> 12:27.903
What are you talking about?
Are you okay?

12:28.206 --> 12:29.321
| am concerned about you.

12:29.624 --> 12:30.989
Are you concerned about me, huh?

12:31.292 --> 12:33.750
Or are you concerned
I'm gonna prove you were lying?

12:34.045 --> 12:37.208
Because if we had Thai food,
as you "claim",

12:37.507 --> 12:39.089
then I would have a receipt
still in my wallet,

12:39.384 --> 12:40.465
since I don't file
my receipts

12:40.760 --> 12:42.626
until the end of the week.

12:42.929 --> 12:44.920
Aha!
Aha!

12:45.223 --> 12:47.464
Wait.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.098
It's a receipt.
What?

12:49.394 --> 12:50.475
For Thai food

12:50.770 --> 12:52.352
that we ordered
on Thursday.

12:52.647 --> 12:53.853
Well...

12:54.148 --> 12:55.604
You know what? Fine.

12:55.900 --> 12:58.642
But if we used our faux throw
as you say we did,

12:58.945 --> 13:00.481
then I will still
have chinchilla fur

13:00.780 --> 13:03.568
on my sweatpants.
On his sweatpants.

13:03.866 --> 13:05.027
Aha!

13:05.326 --> 13:06.691
Aha!

13:06.995 --> 13:09.453
Wait.
Karen's been chinchilla'd.

13:09.747 --> 13:11.829
You named your sweatpants?
| name what I name.

13:12.125 --> 13:13.365
Just so you know,

13:13.668 --> 13:15.250
| scheduled you a consultation
with Dr. Wu.

13:15.545 --> 13:16.660
No.

13:16.963 --> 13:18.374
You said we had popcorn
that night, right?

13:18.673 --> 13:20.084
Hm-mm.
Whenever I have popcorn,

13:20.383 --> 13:22.875
| always get the little kernels
stuck in my chompers.

13:23.177 --> 13:25.544
Ah...
Ah...

13:25.847 --> 13:26.837
Nothing.

13:27.140 --> 13:28.346
There's nothing.

13:28.641 --> 13:30.302
Aha!
Aha!

13:30.601 --> 13:32.888
Hold up. That's a husk.
That is a husk.

13:33.187 --> 13:34.723
JANE:
| hope you're satisfied.

13:35.023 --> 13:36.184
DAVE:
Hey, how did you...?

13:36.482 --> 13:37.938
But...
[CAT PURRING]

13:38.234 --> 13:40.350
But...
Where did you get that?

13:40.653 --> 13:42.189
We're catsitting
for the Carters.

13:42.488 --> 13:43.523
| told you that.

13:43.823 --> 13:45.029
[BRAD SIGHS]

13:45.325 --> 13:46.815
Is it possible
| imagined the whole thing?

13:47.869 --> 13:50.987
| don't know, but I'll say this:
Even though tomorrow

13:51.289 --> 13:54.702
| may have no recollection
of what we did in here,

13:55.001 --> 13:57.618
| will always remember it
in here.

13:57.920 --> 13:59.957
We had a good run, didn't we?
Sure did, man.

14:00.256 --> 14:02.338
Bring it in, big fella.
All right.

14:02.633 --> 14:04.249
Uh...

14:04.552 --> 14:05.758
Can I help you, dudes?

14:06.054 --> 14:08.466
Yeah, man.
I'm just gonna return this DVD

14:08.765 --> 14:10.347
and pay the late fee.

14:10.641 --> 14:12.257
You know women
and Mamma Mial,

14:12.560 --> 14:14.267
can't tear it away
from them.

14:14.562 --> 14:17.224
There is no late fee.
No late fee?

14:17.523 --> 14:18.638
My wife rented this
three days ago

14:18.941 --> 14:20.306
because she
loves it so much,

14:20.610 --> 14:22.442
whereas I'm partial to karate
and brief nudity.

14:22.737 --> 14:24.603
| don't know what to tell you.
There's no late fee.

14:24.906 --> 14:27.819
It was rented this morning.
BOTH: Aha!

14:31.829 --> 14:35.163
Okay. The egg's almost done.
We are gonna win this thing.

14:35.458 --> 14:37.574
Max, what are you doing?
Grant loved bacon.

14:37.877 --> 14:39.834
What?
Can't even enjoy it anymore.

14:40.129 --> 14:41.540
Snap out of it.
You can't get sad

14:41.839 --> 14:42.920
every time
you think about bacon.

14:43.216 --> 14:44.627
Bacon's gonna come up a lot
for you.

14:44.926 --> 14:46.542
| kKnow.

14:46.844 --> 14:48.710
Well, look who decided
to finally show up.

14:49.013 --> 14:50.048
Took you long enough.

14:50.348 --> 14:52.510
You're slow,
just like your baby.

14:52.809 --> 14:53.799
Oh, my God.
| didn't mean that.

14:54.102 --> 14:55.558
| meant
because your baby's late.

14:55.853 --> 14:58.811
But I think your baby is gonna
be super fast and awesome.

14:59.107 --> 15:01.348
No. No!
This is my time to shine!

15:01.651 --> 15:02.891
Unh. Oh, my God.

15:03.194 --> 15:04.480
| think I'm going into labor.
What?

15:04.779 --> 15:05.860
Our perfect miracle's coming.

15:06.155 --> 15:07.691
Get your Bobby Kennedy hands
off me.

15:07.990 --> 15:09.321
Unh!
Okay. What can I do to help?

15:09.617 --> 15:11.358
Chair.

15:11.661 --> 15:13.117
[LAUGHS]

15:13.413 --> 15:15.495
Justin, sandwich me.

15:15.790 --> 15:17.997
What are you doing?
But that's my egg!

15:18.292 --> 15:19.703
I'm sure you froze
some of your own,

15:20.002 --> 15:22.289
but in case you didn't,
good luck.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.671
[MOUTHS]
No!

15:25.967 --> 15:28.174
[240]

15:43.276 --> 15:46.189
[SIGHS]
Well,

15:46.487 --> 15:47.727
you lose some,
you lose some, right?

15:48.030 --> 15:50.772
Oh! Nothing ever changes.

15:51.075 --> 15:52.315
Julie will always be a winner.

15:52.618 --> 15:55.485
| will always be a loser.
Let's just go home.

15:55.788 --> 15:57.779
[GRUNTS]

15:58.082 --> 15:59.538
| didn't wanna do this,
but I will.

15:59.834 --> 16:01.199
Penny, we are not going out
like this.

16:01.502 --> 16:04.164
Me crying about Grant,
you crying about your stuff.

16:04.464 --> 16:07.001
| wasn't paying attention.
This is our John Hughes film,

16:07.300 --> 16:08.711
and those two
are clearly the bad guys,

16:09.010 --> 16:10.421
one being little and blond
and fit,

16:10.720 --> 16:11.881
the other looking
like Greg Kinnear,

16:12.180 --> 16:13.796
they are so clearly
not Jewish.

16:14.098 --> 16:16.931
| don't need to tell you this.
You are the assistant curator

16:17.226 --> 16:18.887
to the original
John Hughes Museum,

16:19.187 --> 16:20.677
which,
for purpose of this pep talk,

16:20.980 --> 16:22.311
| will choose to believe
is a real thing

16:22.607 --> 16:24.189
and not the first act
of an after school special.

16:24.484 --> 16:26.600
Thank you.
You're welcome.

16:26.903 --> 16:29.395
Pick up the egg. Let's go.
Okay, okay, okay.

16:29.697 --> 16:31.358
These WASPs are gonna beat us.

16:31.657 --> 16:33.568
To the Kerkovich way.

16:33.868 --> 16:35.199
Dave will never know the truth.

16:35.495 --> 16:37.987
The movie was rented today!

16:38.289 --> 16:39.871
| slept with Dave.
Alex.

16:40.166 --> 16:41.497
| knew it.
Admit it, Jane.

16:41.792 --> 16:43.328
It was all a cover-up.

16:45.171 --> 16:48.630
Fine. It was a cover-up.
Yeah.

16:48.925 --> 16:51.462
Alex made up a story,
| gave it life,

16:51.761 --> 16:54.628
and it was beautiful.

16:54.931 --> 16:57.389
First,
| took your precious Karen

16:57.683 --> 16:58.798
while you were in the shower

16:59.101 --> 17:01.513
and I planted the faux fur.

17:01.812 --> 17:05.146
Then I traced Pattaya That's
logo on receipt paper,

17:05.441 --> 17:07.432
typed up take-out orders,
forged your signature

17:07.734 --> 17:10.522
before putting it all
in your wallet.

17:10.820 --> 17:12.732
Then my signature moment,

17:13.031 --> 17:14.739
one that will rival
Grandma Senka

17:15.034 --> 17:16.444
in Kerkovich history.

17:18.538 --> 17:23.078
The insertion of the popcorn
while you were sleeping.

17:23.376 --> 17:25.492
[COUGHS]

17:25.795 --> 17:28.162
And I would have gotten away
with it too,

17:28.464 --> 17:31.001
if it weren't for Aleksandra.

17:31.300 --> 17:33.962
[IN SERBIAN]

17:40.184 --> 17:42.846
This is hot.
Right? It is hot.

17:43.145 --> 17:44.601
"To get to Rosalita's,

17:44.897 --> 17:47.013
take this untouchable
means of transportation.”

17:47.316 --> 17:48.556
Baby carriages,

17:48.859 --> 17:50.520
from the train station scene
in The Untouchables.

17:50.820 --> 17:52.777
Oh, shopping carts.
Grant and I'd

17:53.072 --> 17:54.904
go to the supermarket and
play Supermarket Sweep.

17:55.199 --> 17:57.907
You really miss him, don't you?
Not everything's about Grant.

17:58.202 --> 18:00.034
| just happen to be great
at picking a winning cart.

18:00.329 --> 18:01.694
Okay.
A-bup-bup-bup!

18:01.998 --> 18:04.160
That one's got a fish wheel.
Ugh!

18:04.458 --> 18:05.539
You gotta let the
cart pick you.

18:05.835 --> 18:08.372
This one's telling me
not to pick it.

18:08.671 --> 18:10.287
Ooh.
She's got some nice ride.

18:10.590 --> 18:12.126
But something bad happened
in here.

18:12.425 --> 18:13.790
Are you serious right now?
A hate crime.

18:14.093 --> 18:16.209
A baby committed a hate crime
on another baby.

18:16.512 --> 18:18.094
[SIGHS]
This one.

18:18.389 --> 18:19.754
This war horse
is born to run.

18:20.057 --> 18:22.219
Yes, she is! Yes!

18:22.518 --> 18:24.680
[SCREAMS AND GRUNTS]

18:24.979 --> 18:26.720
What a graceful swan of a lady.

18:27.023 --> 18:28.138
You went through
a lot of trouble

18:28.441 --> 18:29.556
to pretend
we didn't sleep together.

18:29.859 --> 18:31.315
Are you really that upset
about it?

18:31.611 --> 18:34.319
No, but we're in such a great
place right now as friends

18:34.614 --> 18:37.151
and that's important to me,
and then this happened.

18:37.450 --> 18:40.112
| just wasn't ready to open
that rabbit hole.

18:40.411 --> 18:41.901
Go down that rabbit hole.

18:42.204 --> 18:44.912
Oh, Dave, clean it up.

18:45.207 --> 18:47.039
Anyway, I guess
for the sake of friendship,

18:47.335 --> 18:48.700
| was afraid
to talk about it.

18:50.004 --> 18:52.462
Talk about what?
Us having sex.

18:52.757 --> 18:54.213
We didn't have sex.

18:54.508 --> 18:56.090
Dave, you literally spent
two full days

18:56.385 --> 18:58.717
trying to get me
to admit--

18:59.013 --> 18:59.969
<i>On...</i>

19:00.264 --> 19:01.629
<i>On...</i>

19:02.933 --> 19:04.674
Thanks.
You're welcome.

19:04.977 --> 19:07.594
[SHOPPING CARTS RATTLING]

19:07.897 --> 19:09.137
JULIE:
Go, go!

19:09.440 --> 19:11.147
[JULIE YELLING IN SPANISH]

19:11.442 --> 19:14.480
PENNY: How did you
know | froze my eggs?

19:14.779 --> 19:17.271
Oh, she just kicked.
She can feel us winning.

19:17.573 --> 19:18.654
[240]

19:18.949 --> 19:20.565
Go, go!

19:20.868 --> 19:23.826
Faster! Hyah! Hyah!

19:24.121 --> 19:26.783
JULIE:
Aah! Go, go, go!

19:27.083 --> 19:29.495
MAX:
| should have eaten more bacon.

19:29.794 --> 19:31.535
[240]

19:36.300 --> 19:37.381
Face it, Penny.

19:37.677 --> 19:39.293
You will always be
second best.

19:39.595 --> 19:41.586
People read your books
on the toilet!

19:42.932 --> 19:44.889
[IN SLOW-MOTION VOICE]
No!

19:46.894 --> 19:48.931
MAX: Something's going
wrong with their wheel.

19:49.230 --> 19:51.597
[ALL SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

19:54.985 --> 19:56.396
[CROWD CHEERING]

20:02.451 --> 20:05.159
No!
[PENNY CHEERS]

20:05.454 --> 20:07.912
Yes! Whoo!

20:08.207 --> 20:10.790
Yes! We did it!

20:11.085 --> 20:12.575
Life moves pretty fast.

20:12.878 --> 20:14.744
If you don't stop and look
around, you could miss it.

20:15.047 --> 20:16.208
Who you talking to?
Scotty.

20:16.507 --> 20:17.747
Hey. Congrats, you guys.

20:18.050 --> 20:19.165
Here's your trophy

20:19.468 --> 20:20.208
plus a whole bunch
of Foot Locker key chains

20:21.262 --> 20:23.629
and one of these metal things
they use to measure your feet.

20:23.931 --> 20:26.013
Nice size 10s.
How did you know that?

20:26.308 --> 20:28.720
I'm into feet. Big feet.

20:29.019 --> 20:30.054
PENNY:
Ew. Ew. Gross.

20:30.354 --> 20:31.560
Awesome.
You're welcome.

20:31.856 --> 20:35.895
All right, you two,
let's smile for the camera.

20:36.193 --> 20:37.649
[CAMERA BEEPS]

20:40.322 --> 20:41.528
[240]

20:41.824 --> 20:43.064
Babe, I am so sorry.

20:43.367 --> 20:45.654
| will never Kerkovich-way
you again.

20:47.037 --> 20:48.152
What can I do
to make it up to you?

20:48.456 --> 20:49.617
[GRUNTS]

20:49.915 --> 20:51.576
I'll get you ice cream.

20:54.837 --> 20:56.874
I'll let you eat it
in bed...

20:59.467 --> 21:02.004
...off my body...

21:02.303 --> 21:04.089
[SIGHS]

21:04.388 --> 21:06.004
...while we listen

21:06.307 --> 21:08.799
to your favorite
Steve Martin banjo album...

21:09.101 --> 21:10.262
Hmm?

21:10.561 --> 21:11.676
[GROANS]

21:13.063 --> 21:15.020
...every night
for the next week?

21:15.316 --> 21:17.273
Month? Year?

21:18.736 --> 21:20.477
You stay here.
I'll be right back.

21:22.198 --> 21:24.735
Guilt trips,
my feline friend,

21:25.034 --> 21:26.524
that's the Williams way.
